PROFESSOR CLARK WAS TELLING A STORY ABOUT HIS EXPERIENCE, AND APPRECIATION FOR, GROWING UP IN A PUBLIC LIBRARY.
MR. CLARK BEGINS THE STORY AS A BOY, AND DESCRIBES HOW HE THOUGHT HIS FAMILY WAS RICH BUT HIS PARENTS SAID "NOPE, WE ARE POOR".
HE DESCRIBES HOW HIS DAD USED TO WAX THE FLOORS AND THE TOPS OF THE BOOKSHELVES SO THAT THE FLOORS GLEAMED AND THE SHELVES WOULD GLEAM AS YOU WENT UP THE STAIRS AND LOOKED DOWN AT THEM.
PROFESSOR CLARK DIDN'T HAVE FRIENDS OVER MUCH OR AT ALL BECAUSE HE SOMETIMES WANTED TO BE NORMAL, BUT HE IN FACT "LIVED IN THE LIBRARY!
WHEN HE WAS A BOY, IF HE COULDN'T SLEEP OR WANTED TO KNOW AN ANSWER TO SOMETHING, HE WOULD GET OUT OF BED AND GO DOWN TO THE LIBRARY AND READ UNTIL 3AM
DURING THE DAY, HE HAD TO BE QUIET IN THE LIBRARY, BUT AT NIGHT HE WAS THE ONLY KID IN THE LIBRARY AND COULD RUN THROUGH THE SHELVES HOLLERING AS HE PLEASED.
HIS THIRST FOR KNOWLEDGE LED HIM TO GO TO COLLEGE AND GET AN EDUCATION.
WHEN HE TOOK A POSITION AT A COLLEGE AS A PROFESSOR, HE PROUDLY SHOWED HIS FATHER THE DOOR TO HIS CLASSROOM LABELED "PROFESSOR CLARK" AND THE LOOK ON HIS DAD'S FACE SHOWED HIS PRIDE
HE CREDITS HIS DESIRE TO HAVE KNOWLEDGE AND PURSUE EDUCATION TO HIS CHILDHOOD GROWING UP IN THE LIBRARY
RONALD'S DAD WAS A CUSTODIAN AT A PUBLIC LIBRARY
HIS DAD WAXED THE FLOORS SO THERE WAS NEVER ANY TRASH OR BUBBLEGUM
HIS DAD EVEN WAXED THE TOP OF THE BOOKSHELVES
RONALD THOUGHT HIS FAMILY WAS RICH BUT HIS PARENTS DISAGREED
RONALD WOULD HAVE TO BE QUIET IN THE LIBRARY DURING THE DAY BUT COULD RUN AROUND THE SHELVES AT NIGHT AS LOUD AS HE WANTED
SOME NIGHTS HE WOULD STAY UP UNTIL 3AM READING BOOKS AND LEARNING IN THE "TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE"
HE NEVER HAD FRIENDS OVER FROM SCHOOL BECAUSE HE WAS EMBARRASSED THAT HIS FAMILY LIVED IN THE LIBRARY
RONALD WENT OFF TO COLLEGE TO GET A DEGREE
HE THEN BECAME A PROFESSOR AT A COLLEGE AND SHOWED HIS DAD THE NAMEPLATE THAT SAID "PROFESSOR CLARK"
HIS DAD WAS QUIET WHEN HE SAW BUT RONALD COULD TELL BY THE LOOK IN HIS EYE THAT HE WAS PROUD OF HIS SON
RONALD CREDITS LIVING IN THE LIBRARY WITH GIVING HIM A THIRST FOR KNOWLEDGE
